      "content": "thanks. valgrind is definitely out since our target hardware is too constrained for that kind of overhead. i've checked the main loop and most of the lifecycle management seems solid, but the leak is really subtle. it's like it's creeping up in the background. \n\nis there a way to use static analysis or specific compiler flags to catch these kinds of \"hidden\" allocations that might be happening in deeper nested calls or within third-party driver code? i need something more automated than just manual code review.",
      "source": "evaluator"
